    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n3802" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔρρω</span></b>  (<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ϝέρρω</span>): <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">go</span> with pain or difficulty, <i><span class="en">Od. 4.367</span></i>; of the lame Hephaestus, <i><span class="en">Il. 18.421</span></i>; esp. imp. as imprecation,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔρρε, ἔρρετε</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">begone!</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 8.164</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 10.72</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">75,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 24.239</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            ἐρρέτω</span>, ‘off with him!’ <i><span class="en">Od.
            5.139</span></i>; ‘let him go to Perdition!’ <i><span class="en">Il. 9.377</span></i>; similarly the part., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐνθάδε
            ϝέρρων</span>, ‘coming hither, to my ruin,’ <i><span class="en">Il. 8.239</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il.
            9.364</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
